    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-13T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-13T15:00:00-05:00" n="600"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d600">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/145</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d600fn1">The same, on the same date, to the
                        Ambassador in Japan. (File No. 862.85/181.)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-13T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 13, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your cipher telegram September 10, 8 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d600fn2">Not
                        printed.</note> The Department has agreed with the British Government to the
                    following scheme of allocation of the German and Austrian vessels in China:
                    [Here follows the latter half of the British Embassy’s memorandum of October
                        1.<note n="3" xml:id="d600fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_690">p. 690</ref>.</note>]
                    Consult with your British colleague and endeavor to secure this arrangement. For
                    your guidance the Department is opposed to the recognition of the claims of any
                    private parties that they have purchased <pb facs="0768" n="694" xml:id="pg_694"
                    /> any of these vessels. You will endeavor to prevent recognition of such
                    claims.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
